    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Another Setback For Supermarket in Hastings</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By ELSA BRENNER</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New York State Supreme Court Justice Peter Leavitt upholds Hastings-on-Hudson planning board's rejection of plan by Big V Supermarkets to open ShopRite supermarket (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>ShopRite's five-year effort to open a supermarket in Hastings-on-Hudson experienced another setback when Justice Peter M. Leavitt of State Supreme Court in White Plains upheld the village Planning Board's rejection of the store plans.</p>
        <p>Judge Leavitt said the board acted properly and followed state standards for environmental reviews when it rejected plans by Big V Supermarkets of Florida, N.Y., for the supermarket on Route 9A.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>ShopRite's five-year effort to open a supermarket in Hastings-on-Hudson experienced another setback when Justice Peter M. Leavitt of State Supreme Court in White Plains upheld the village Planning Board's rejection of the store plans.</p>
        <p>Judge Leavitt said the board acted properly and followed state standards for environmental reviews when it rejected plans by Big V Supermarkets of Florida, N.Y., for the supermarket on Route 9A.</p>
        <p>Residents have argued that the market would worsen traffic, pollute the Saw Mill River and endanger smaller shops.</p>
        <p>For 13 years, Big V has been trying to build a new ShopRite in Greenburgh and its villages.</p>
        <p>ELSA BRENNER</p>
        <p>IN BUSINESS</p>
      </block>
